'''Mustafa Saadoon Abbood Al-Korji''' ({{langx|ar|مصطفى سعدون}}; born 25 May 2001) is an Iraqi professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right back]] for [[Iraq Stars League]] club [[Al-Shorta SC|Al-Shorta]] and the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq national team]].

==Club career==
Born in Corgi, Saadoon spent his youth career at the [[RCD Espanyol]] football academy in [[Baghdad]]. In 2022, he joined [[Al-Kahrabaa SC|Al-Kahrabaa]] and played there during one season before joining Iraqi giant [[Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya]] in August 2023.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=1258730 |title=القوة الجوية يحسم صفقتي علي جاسم وسعدون |trans-title=Al-Quwa Al-Jawiya concludes the deals for Ali Jassim and Saadoun |publisher=Koora |date=2 August 2023 |language=ar |access-date=1 May 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
On 13 October 2023, Saadoon made his international debut for [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]] in the team's goalless draw against [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]], as part of the [[2023 Jordan International Tournament]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://almaalomah.me/news/43685/sports/%D8%AF%D9%88%D9%84%D9%8A-%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%82:-%D9%87%D8%B0%D8%A7-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AB%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%8A-%D9%83%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%B2-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8A |title=دولي سابق: هذا الثنائي كان الأبرز في المنتخب العراقي |trans-title=Former international: This duo was the most prominent in the Iraqi national team |date=14 October 2023 |publisher=Al Maalomah |language=ar |access-date=1 May 2024}}</ref>

In April 2024, Saadoon featured in [[Iraq national under-23 football team|Iraq U23]]'s squad for the [[2024 AFC U-23 Asian Cup]]. In the last group stage match against [[Saudi Arabia national under-23 football team|Saudi Arabia]], he won a penalty for his team and later scored himself the winning goal for Iraq as the match ended in a 2–1 win for them, thus qualify Iraq to the quarter-finals as the group winner despite losing their first game.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.alkhaleej.ae/2024-04-22/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84%D9%85%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%AA%D8%A3%D9%87%D9%84-%D8%A5%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AB%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%A8%D8%A8%D8%B7%D9%88%D9%84%D8%A9-%D8%A2%D8%B3%D9%8A%D8%A7/%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9-%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A8%D9%8A/%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9 |title=الأولمبي العراقي يتأهل إلى دور الثمانية ببطولة آسيا |trans-title=The Iraqi Olympic team qualifies for the quarter-finals of the Asian Championship |date=22 April 2024 |publisher=Al Khaleej |language=ar |access-date=1 May 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.winwin.com/%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/5-%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A8%D9%8A%D9%86-%D9%88%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%A1-%D8%AA%D8%A3%D9%87%D9%84-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84%D9%85%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8A-%D8%A5%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%B1%D8%A8%D8%B9-%D9%86%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%8A-%D9%83%D8%A3%D8%B3-%D8%A2%D8%B3%D9%8A%D8%A7 |title=5 لاعبين وراء تأهل الأولمبي العراقي إلى ربع نهائي كأس آسيا |trans-title=5 players behind Iraq's Olympic team's qualification to the AFC Asian Cup quarter-finals |date=22 April 2024 |publisher=winwin |language=ar |access-date=1 May 2024}}</ref> Saadoun continoued to feature for the team as they finished third overall in the tournament and qualified to the [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics|2024 Olympic games]]

